Proetor. “As praetor.'’ Anciently all magistrates were called praetors. Thus the dictator is stylcd proetor maximus by Livy, vii. 3. Subsequently the name was attached to particular magistrates, who rankcd next to the consul. There were two only of them, while the Roman Empire was confined to Italy.
